Mix the dried fruit with the sugar, cinnamon sticks, mixed spice, cloves, grated nutmeg and citrus zest in a large bowl.Pour over the vodka, and cover tightly with cling film.Place in the fridge and leave for 3 days, stirring once each day.Line a sieve with a double layer of fine muslin and place over a large, clean jug.Pour the dried fruit and vodka mixture into the sieve and allow to drip through into the jug.Pour into a sterilized bottle.